</caption>
<paragraph id="FEA5DA6211B28C02A069B7BC850B9E1D" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="93" pageId="4" pageNumber="91">
Head transversely trapezoidal, with dense and deep punctures, slightly depressed in front; black elongate setae on temples. Antennae short (Fig. 4a), extending to or a little beyond the base of pronotum; antennomeres short, particularly V-VII. Pronotum transversely subexagonal (Fig. 4a), maximal width just anterior to the middle, sides 
<pageBreakToken id="DFEBD82DA4563F937F36C9861303239C" pageId="5" pageNumber="92" start="start">subrounded</pageBreakToken>
in the basal half; in the middle with a slight mid-longitudinal depression; punctures slightly sparser than on head. Scutellum subrectangular, rounded at apex, with long black setae particularly on sides. Elytra weakly convex only on the basal third, subrugose, with long whitish setae, denser posteriorly and on lateral margins. 
<pageBreakToken id="779A56D0031CCAEC7629BF0AF6D4B390" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" start="start">Ventral</pageBreakToken>
side with dense and long whitish setation. Legs not modified; tibiae straight; all legs with two tibial spurs, fore and middle slender, posterior spurs spatuliform, external spur wider; claws distinctly curved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B5D9A2CF6E450FDD13E67B5946114C07" pageId="6" pageNumber="93">The single female does not correspond to any described species and possibly represents a new undescribed species. We prefer not to describe it and wait for the discovery of the male.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D60897DA1FD4A2F8EF78FB2DCB3A500" pageId="6" pageNumber="93">
Six other species in both Section I and II have a cupreous longitudinal stripe on the elytra: (a) 
<taxonomicName id="427B56381C3D79264F9DECE0D8EE2E35" authority="Semenov, 1894" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Teratolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teratolytta carlae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carlae">Teratolytta carlae</taxonomicName>
Bologna, 2006 (Fig. 4b); 
<taxonomicName id="CD8CE98E2011FC80385353C9E0AA415A" authority="Semenov, 1894" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Teratolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teratolytta kaszabi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaszabi">Teratolytta kaszabi</taxonomicName>
Kryzhanovskij, 1959 (Fig. 4i); 
<taxonomicName id="42BBE4DEF692B3E7AAE4C5EA0F8A692E" authority="Semenov, 1894" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Teratolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teratolytta regina" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="regina">Teratolytta regina</taxonomicName>
Kaszab, 1958; (b) 
<taxonomicName id="FDDF2887F68829EB0B49CEA285DB92A9" authority="Semenov, 1894" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Teratolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teratolytta dives" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dives">Teratolytta dives</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="42DDC3609031161F08693968C058258F" originalValue="Brullé">Brulle</normalizedToken>
, 1832) (Fig. 4c), 
<taxonomicName id="A8CFC5C104649FCF42BDA1CB88D197C4" authority="Semenov, 1894" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Teratolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teratolytta tricolor" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">Teratolytta tricolor</taxonomicName>
(Haag-Rutenberg, 1880), 
<taxonomicName id="9DB09D0097AC4CBCA6695D6C3BA1504C" authority="Semenov, 1894" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Teratolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teratolytta vanensis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vanensis">Teratolytta vanensis</taxonomicName>
Kaszab, 1968 (Fig. 4o). Species A differs from the species in Section II because it has a narrower cupreous elytral stripe, metallic green head and pronotum, distinctly longer antennae, extending to the fore third of elytra, more slender and elongate antennomeres V-VII. Moreover in 
<taxonomicName id="9A91F94861E9041993D580C926A44A64" authority="Semenov, 1894" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Teratolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teratolytta dives" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dives">Teratolytta dives</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1147EB53920D36016E14BBDCE77D7DA2" authority="Semenov, 1894" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Teratolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teratolytta tricolor" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">Teratolytta tricolor</taxonomicName>
the pronotum is wider in front, slightly concave, not rounded with whitish setae and head and pronotum punctures are bigger. Due to the more expanded black coloration of knees and black setation on pronotum and head, the probable new species is more similar to 
<taxonomicName id="9E8A67AEEF717CE8E6BF7A2BA53E8BD4" authority="Semenov, 1894" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Teratolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teratolytta vanensis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vanensis">Teratolytta vanensis</taxonomicName>
, which differs by its notably smaller size, narrower pronotum and distinctly longer antennae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="735D6AA847442B58BDB0CC052399626D" pageId="6" pageNumber="93">
Comparing this new 
<taxonomicName id="500BEABD7FC3D420C633498BE796EAF8" authority="Semenov, 1894" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Teratolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teratolytta" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Teratolytta</taxonomicName>
species with other striped species of Section I, 
<taxonomicName id="BBB3A535E78A8CDA627B912990134F8A" authority="Semenov, 1894" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Teratolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teratolytta kaszabi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaszabi">Teratolytta kaszabi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4D5F75A8229ACD0322B507C66432DDAC" authority="Semenov, 1894" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Teratolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teratolytta regina" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="regina">Teratolytta regina</taxonomicName>
, have slightly longer antennae, similar body size and both are distributed in Central Asia. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName id="2A402F5C1622B79FCFF922E8F7BD0903" authority="Semenov, 1894" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Teratolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teratolytta kaszabi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaszabi">Teratolytta kaszabi</taxonomicName>
has red unicolour knees and more hexagonal and narrower pronotum. The probable new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A0B7F43630AFC50408AF4B449DF8A170" authority="Semenov, 1894" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Teratolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teratolytta carlae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carlae">Teratolytta carlae</taxonomicName>
in colour of setae on head and pronotum, colour of knees and body and the length of antennae, but differs by smaller size, less slender body, and slightly widened posterior portion of elytra. The striped form in 
<taxonomicName id="1562A31630B4258D8E9F6D6B68E1EC18" authority="Semenov, 1894" authorityName="Semenov" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Teratolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Teratolytta carlae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carlae">Teratolytta carlae</taxonomicName>
is a variant and other specimens are uniformly blue.
</paragraph>
